     <actual value="2.00">
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">27-06-2019: At national level, existing policy is still in draft but the Regulatory Impact Assessment that was conducted includes our recommendations. A road map for reviewing the policy is available, to start in 2019. At district level, there is more interest and commitment. There is increased knowledge on the need for wise use of wetlands, more stakeholders have been mapped and are collaborating with PfR team to advocate for scaling up wise use. For example, media, CSOs and community structures hold debates, campaigns. Executive level picking interest and prioritising wetland issues, eg in May 2019, the President passed a directive for wetland protection which has seen cancellation of land tittles in wetlands especially in Kampala and surrounding areas by the Ministry of Lands and Housing.</narrative>
      </comment>
